M a n B i r d â„¢ 2023-01-10 1:56 AM
bitrate is just how much data is being sent into your ears basically, its kinda like how resolution defines picture quality ( to a degree but simpplified explanation ok) bitrate is kinda like the audio resolution. Its most often audible in dense mixes with lots going on and in the higher frequencies. lower bitrates can often lose a bit of the highs and if theyre still there, they can sound artifacty and just mangled in comparison
1
1:57 AM
its hard to explain haha but if youre aware of what to listen for and have the equipment that can play it back so you can hear it clearly , its very obvious sometimes
1:57 AM
lossless just means theres no lowering in the bitrate so all the resolution that was there in the export is still there
